                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-236-off1328 t18301209-236-victim1995"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-236-person1996">
                  THOMAS 
                  FULLWOOD
               <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1996" type="surname" value="FULLWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1996" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1996" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am engineer at the Independent Gas-light and Coke Company. They act under that name, and are authorised to prosecute and defend in that name; I have seen the Act - this iron was laying on the ground in their yard at <placeName id="t18301209-236-crimeloc1331">Haggerstone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-236-crimeloc1331" type="placeName" value="Haggerstone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-236-crimeloc1331" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-236-off1328 t18301209-236-crimeloc1331"></join> - I had not particularly noticed it for a week before it was taken; it was five bars -I found it at the Police-station on the 7th or 8th of December, about eleven o'clock in the morning - it had been made to a pattern of my own invention: I found about a hundred weight and three quarters of it there - I believe the prisoner had been employed on the works by the commissioners of the road, to wheel ballast away which they had purchased.</p>
               <p>Spurling. Q. Had you seen me on the works with a barrow? A. I think I have; but I am not certain of Jacobs.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-236-person1997">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1997" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1997" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-236-person1997" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 7th of December, about a quarter before seven o'clock, I was on duty as a private patrol of St. Leonard, Shoreditch - at the corner of Union-street, leading towards Kingsland, I saw Spurling wheeling a barrow - Jacobs was walking alongside of him; I crossed over, and asked what they had got there - they said, "Some iron:" I asked where they brought it from - they said,"From Kingsland, from Mr. Perry's marine-store shop;" I said they must go with me to the watch-house, and while I was talking to them, Jacobs slipped two shovels from behind his back - I put them into the barrow, and with the assistance of the Policeman, took them to the station: the shovels have not been claimed - I was present when Fullwood saw the iron at the office, and claimed it; I was sure that Perry did not keep an iron shop at Kingsland.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Spurling's Defence. I went down to my father's to do some work; I was coming up and happened to see the barrow in the road - Jacobs said, "Will you give me a help along with it?" I did not know but it was his property, and wheeled it for him - Smith said, "What have you here?" I said, "Iron;" he said, "I can't let you go;" I said, "Well, I may as well go, it is not my property."</p>
               <p>WILLIAM SMITH. Jacobs said he brought it from an old iron shop - Spurling did not contradict him; he said he had wheeled the barrow for him.</p>
               <p>SPURLING - <rs id="t18301209-236-verdict1332" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18301209-236-verdict1332" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
               <p>JACOBS - <rs id="t18301209-236-verdict1333" type="verdictDescription">
